        "title": 		"Intro",
        "body": <<<"
			<p style="color: red;">Note to self: stop calling these Extras. Call them something beginning with "R".</p>
		
			<p>An 'Extra' is any additional functionality that is added inside of another Component.</p>
			
			<p>I have made Extras very easy to add in the code:</p>

			<code style="background: #dddddd; padding: 0.5rem;">
				&lt;r.hyperlink href="https://google.com:"&gt;Click me!&lt;/r.hyperlink&gt;
			</code>

			<p>All Extras will follow the "r.XXX" naming convention. The "r" stands for "ReactComponent" (which is what "Extras" actually are).</p> 

			<p>Below are some examples of the Extras we have so far, used inside of the <strong>Text</strong> component.</p>
		">>>,
