        "title": 		"Hyperlinks",
        "body": <<<"
			<p>If you ever need to link to an external website, just <r.hyperlink href="https://google.com">do this</r.hyperlink>. The little icon after it indicates that it's an external link.</p>
			
			<p>If you want, I can also let you make hyperlinks which <r.hyperlink href="#c-extra-1-0">scroll you to a certain block</r.hyperlink> (if you need a "go to" type of feature).</p>

			<p>I've added a basic underline animation for now. I don't really want to spend too much time on animation effects when there's so much more to do.</p>

			<p>An important thing to note about hyperlinks: The "unvisited" and "visited" state colours we use for these should also be the ones we use for ALL interactive content in this framework.</p>
